            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-dragon-age-veilguard-tips-guides-1851700522<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="df500b5ad0a64644a69dbb4f1110c84d" data-recommend-id="image://df500b5ad0a64644a69dbb4f1110c84d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Square Enix<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Square Enix<!-- -->, <!-- -->poncle<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://x.com/BeskInfinity/status/1856366545212985370&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://x.com/BeskInfinity/status/1856366545212985370" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BeskInfinity / Rockstar Games / Kotaku</a></span>, <!-- -->Atlus / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->BioWare / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->BioWare / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="df500b5ad0a64644a69dbb4f1110c84d" data-recommend-id="image://df500b5ad0a64644a69dbb4f1110c84d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>From the best decks in <em>Pokémon TCG Pocket </em>to a ludicrously expensive card in the original game—and a bunch of other updates, guides, and recommendations in between—here are the most helpful tips we published this week.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ea8f460bc3151a75cab5115873acd389" data-recommend-id="image://ea8f460bc3151a75cab5115873acd389" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A collection of pairs of Pokemon cards, laid out across a blurred Gardevoir background." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A collection of pairs of Pokemon cards, laid out across a blurred Gardevoir background." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ea8f460bc3151a75cab5115873acd389" data-recommend-id="image://ea8f460bc3151a75cab5115873acd389" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A collection of pairs of Pokemon cards, laid out across a blurred Gardevoir background." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>As <em>Pokémon TCG Pocket </em>completes its second week since launch, players have found the game’s grooves and solid patterns have begun to develop. Core to these are four specific decks that are dominating in online battles, forming a meta that looks unlikely to shift <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-set-expansion-event-schedule-leak-1851694729&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-set-expansion-event-schedule-leak-1851694729">until January’s delivery of a whole new set of cards</a></span>. We’ve put together our best versions of all four decks. - Ethan Gach, John Walker </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-best-decks-mewtwo-charizard-1851696181&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-best-decks-mewtwo-charizard-1851696181">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="826739c93d37277f81d06793d2116d03" data-recommend-id="image://826739c93d37277f81d06793d2116d03" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows GTA SA before and after the update. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><span data-id="826739c93d37277f81d06793d2116d03" data-recommend-id="image://826739c93d37277f81d06793d2116d03" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows GTA SA before and after the update. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Rockstar Games has released updates for each of the remastered<em> Grand Theft Auto</em> games included in the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/rockstar-apologizes-for-busted-gta-trilogy-offers-free-1848090482&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/rockstar-apologizes-for-busted-gta-trilogy-offers-free-1848090482"><em>GTA Trilogy Definitive Edition</em></a></span> collection that make these maligned versions play better, as well as making them look more like the original games released on PS2 back in the early 2000s. - Zack Zwiezen </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-trilogy-vice-city-graphics-update-2024-netflix-ps5-1851696744&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-trilogy-vice-city-graphics-update-2024-netflix-ps5-1851696744">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d59689ea577ef500a1bae8cdea32a8db" data-recommend-id="image://d59689ea577ef500a1bae8cdea32a8db" data-format="jpg" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A woman with blonde hair is in focus in front of a building, her eyes are closed and her hand is raised towards her neck." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A woman with blonde hair is in focus in front of a building, her eyes are closed and her hand is raised towards her neck." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Atlus / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d59689ea577ef500a1bae8cdea32a8db" data-recommend-id="image://d59689ea577ef500a1bae8cdea32a8db" data-format="jpg" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A woman with blonde hair is in focus in front of a building, her eyes are closed and her hand is raised towards her neck." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em> is a stunning RPG that exemplifies almost everything that makes Atlus-developed games great. With the social elements of <em>Persona</em>, battle mechanics from <em>Shin Megami Tensei</em>, a mix of real-time and turn-based combat, and a traditional RPG class system, there is an enormous amount to love about <em>Metaphor</em>. Admittedly, if you are the target demographic for this kind of game, you did not need me to explain all this to you. But in the bizarre chance this is your first time ever hearing about <em>Metaphor</em>, please play this spectacular game. <em>Kotaku</em>’s <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-review-pc-ps5-xbox-persona-atlus-1851665876&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-review-pc-ps5-xbox-persona-atlus-1851665876">Kenneth Sheppard can explain</a></span> to you why you should. - Timothy Monbleau </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metaphor-play-after-persona-ys-final-fantasy-shin-1851698925?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metaphor-play-after-persona-ys-final-fantasy-shin-1851698925?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="42eaa37a7563d86d4ee2df54c63e3b21" data-recommend-id="image://42eaa37a7563d86d4ee2df54c63e3b21" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Pikachu ex card on a blurred background of its own art." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The Pikachu ex card on a blurred background of its own art." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="42eaa37a7563d86d4ee2df54c63e3b21" data-recommend-id="image://42eaa37a7563d86d4ee2df54c63e3b21" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Pikachu ex card on a blurred background of its own art." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Every now and then, there’s a specific card in a specific set of the Pokémon TCG that absolutely blows up beyond all sense. Recent examples include last year’s Iono full-art trainer card, part of Japan’s Clay Burst set, which proved so popular that <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-trading-card-game-tcg-stock-japan-iono-grusha-1850349547&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-trading-card-game-tcg-stock-japan-iono-grusha-1850349547">Japan sold out of all Pokémon cards!</a></span> We’re not quite there yet with Surging Spark’s Pikachu ex, but the card is seeing prices unheard of in the interim. - John Walker </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pikachu-ex-surging-sparks-1851694945?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pikachu-ex-surging-sparks-1851694945?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9126c6383481fceb02ac9dd0eebe44a8" data-recommend-id="image://9126c6383481fceb02ac9dd0eebe44a8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Emmrich, Bellara, Rook, Neve, and Davrin look at something off-screen with concerned expressions." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Emmrich, Bellara, Rook, Neve, and Davrin look at something off-screen with concerned expressions." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->BioWare / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9126c6383481fceb02ac9dd0eebe44a8" data-recommend-id="image://9126c6383481fceb02ac9dd0eebe44a8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Emmrich, Bellara, Rook, Neve, and Davrin look at something off-screen with concerned expressions." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-4-review-dreadwolf-rook-action-rpg-1851681954&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-4-review-dreadwolf-rook-action-rpg-1851681954"><em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em></a></span><em> </em>is a game about choice and consequence. One of the decisions that has the most immediate impact happens at the beginning of the game’s final quest. The effect <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-team-decision-davrin-harding-save-1851694983&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-team-decision-davrin-harding-save-1851694983">this decision</a></span> has on the remainder of the game and, presumably, any future <em>Dragon Age</em> games, has devastated fans in the kind of “hurts so good” way hard choices in video games do. But some fans are not so sure things are as they seem at the end of the game. Is it cope, or is there reason to believe an affected character could still appear in a future <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://howl.link/7y0p8im54aetx&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://howl.link/7y0p8im54aetx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Dragon Age</em></a></span>? - Kenneth Shepard </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-harding-davrin-death-alive-survive-1851697615?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-harding-davrin-death-alive-survive-1851697615?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6cdb818f8b9aa8b101040ef316086b97" data-recommend-id="image://6cdb818f8b9aa8b101040ef316086b97" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Official artwork for Dragon Quest III HD-2D. Four people are riding a large bird as it soars through the air." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Official artwork for Dragon Quest III HD-2D. Four people are riding a large bird as it soars through the air." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6cdb818f8b9aa8b101040ef316086b97" data-recommend-id="image://6cdb818f8b9aa8b101040ef316086b97" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Official artwork for Dragon Quest III HD-2D. Four people are riding a large bird as it soars through the air." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Dragon Quest III HD-2D Remake</em> is the epitome of a new twist on an old classic. At its core, this HD-2D remake plays like an NES or SNES game with a fresh coat of paint. Yet, by the same token, it injects several new features and quality-of-life adjustments that will make this version of <em>Dragon Quest III</em> feel new for even longtime fans. I should know, as I played <em>Dragon Quest III</em> just a few years ago and was shocked by how long it took me to get my bearings. Fighters and Martial Artists start with MP bars? Is this even <em>Dragon Quest III</em>!? - Timothy Monbleau </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-quest-3-hd-2d-remake-guide-tips-seeds-1851698701&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-quest-3-hd-2d-remake-guide-tips-seeds-1851698701">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7799f865699879807473638361141a4b" data-recommend-id="image://7799f865699879807473638361141a4b" data-format="jpg" data-width="851" data-height="480" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario pumps his fist in the air while driving. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mario pumps his fist in the air while driving. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7799f865699879807473638361141a4b" data-recommend-id="image://7799f865699879807473638361141a4b" data-format="jpg" data-width="851" data-height="480" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario pumps his fist in the air while driving. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>With Thanksgiving just a couple of weeks away, Nintendo has announced <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.nintendo.com/us/whatsnew/nintendo-announces-black-friday-offers-providing-even-more-ways-to-play-this-holiday-season/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.nintendo.com/us/whatsnew/nintendo-announces-black-friday-offers-providing-even-more-ways-to-play-this-holiday-season/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">its Black Friday 2024 highlights</a></span>. While there aren’t any standout deals among them, there’s still some decent discounts for anyone who was planning on buying a new Switch or a critically acclaimed game from the console’s back catalog.  - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-black-friday-2024-deals-mk8-zelda-totk-1851696187?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-black-friday-2024-deals-mk8-zelda-totk-1851696187?_gl=1*ibiwtg*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e3d083fcca667827977fe8d489896243" data-recommend-id="image://e3d083fcca667827977fe8d489896243" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Four humans dressed in fantasy attire sit around a campfire. Blue slimes can be seen in the distance." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Four humans dressed in fantasy attire sit around a campfire. Blue slimes can be seen in the distance." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e3d083fcca667827977fe8d489896243" data-recommend-id="image://e3d083fcca667827977fe8d489896243" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Four humans dressed in fantasy attire sit around a campfire. Blue slimes can be seen in the distance." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Dragon Quest III HD-2D Remake</em> may have beautiful, updated graphics, but the soul of this adventure is as old-school as ever. As one of the first tasks of your adventure, you’ll need to make your way over to Patty’s Party Planning Place to recruit three companions. Whether you choose to take along the premade characters or create your own allies, you’ll see that each character can assume one of eight classes. With no frame of reference for how each class performs, how on earth are you supposed to choose? - Timothy Monbleau </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-quest-3-hd-2d-remake-class-guide-1851698849?_gl=1*bb6cqb*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-quest-3-hd-2d-remake-class-guide-1851698849?_gl=1*bb6cqb*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="dfef992e873fa966c2671879969d3921" data-recommend-id="image://dfef992e873fa966c2671879969d3921" data-format="png" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A cast of characters are arranged in promotional art for Vampire Survivors." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A cast of characters are arranged in promotional art for Vampire Survivors." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->poncle</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="dfef992e873fa966c2671879969d3921" data-recommend-id="image://dfef992e873fa966c2671879969d3921" data-format="png" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A cast of characters are arranged in promotional art for Vampire Survivors." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Vampire Survivors</em> draws tons of inspiration from <em>Castlevania</em>, so it is no surprise that the new <em>Ode To Castlevania </em>DLC is fantastic. I’m here to guide you through unlocking each Hero and evolving each weapon, because that’s how you’ll end up accessing everything the<em> Ode To Castlevania </em>level has to offer. After all, What is <em>Vampire Survivors </em>but a delightful little pile of characters and weapons? - Brian Barnett </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/vampire-survivors-ode-to-castlevania-dlc-unlock-hero-1851697959?_gl=1*bb6cqb*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/vampire-survivors-ode-to-castlevania-dlc-unlock-hero-1851697959?_gl=1*bb6cqb*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="582a45ef877963149408274866c284d4" data-recommend-id="image://582a45ef877963149408274866c284d4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The cast of Dragon Age: The Veilguard looks at Davrin as he speaks." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The cast of Dragon Age: The Veilguard looks at Davrin as he speaks." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->BioWare / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="582a45ef877963149408274866c284d4" data-recommend-id="image://582a45ef877963149408274866c284d4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The cast of Dragon Age: The Veilguard looks at Davrin as he speaks." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-4-review-dreadwolf-rook-action-rpg-1851681954&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-4-review-dreadwolf-rook-action-rpg-1851681954"><em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em></a></span><em> </em>has a lot of choices for you to make, especially surrounding its <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-best-companions-lucanis-taash-neve-1851688830&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-best-companions-lucanis-taash-neve-1851688830">seven companions</a></span>. But one of the most significant happens in the game’s final stretch and involves the dwarven rogue Harding and Grey Warden warrior Davrin. If you’re reading this, you’ve likely encountered the consequences of it and are looking to see if that’s how it <em>had</em> to go down. So here’s your guide to that big decision. Spoilers ahead! - Kenneth Shepard </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-team-decision-davrin-harding-save-1851694983?_gl=1*bb6cqb*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-team-decision-davrin-harding-save-1851694983?_gl=1*bb6cqb*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTg1NjgxOC4zMjguMS4xNzMxODU2OTk2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
